    <bp:comment rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#string">FUNCTION May affect the rate of fibrils formation.SUBUNIT Binds to type I and type II collagen, fibronectin and TGF-beta. Forms a ternary complex with MFAP2 and ELN. Interacts with DPT (By similarity).TISSUE SPECIFICITY Detected in placenta (at protein level) (PubMed:32337544). Detected in cerebrospinal fluid, fibroblasts and urine (at protein level) (PubMed:25326458, PubMed:36213313).PTM The attached glycosaminoglycan chain can be either chondroitin sulfate or dermatan sulfate depending upon the tissue of origin.SIMILARITY Belongs to the small leucine-rich proteoglycan (SLRP) family. SLRP class I subfamily.</bp:comment>
  </bp:ProteinReference>
