    <bp:name rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#string">UniProt:O15232 MATN3</bp:name>
    <bp:name rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#string">MATN3</bp:name>
    <bp:xref rdf:resource="#UnificationXref458" />
    <bp:comment rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#string">FUNCTION Major component of the extracellular matrix of cartilage and may play a role in the formation of extracellular filamentous networks.SUBUNIT Can form homooligomers (monomers, dimers, trimers and tetramers) and heterooligomers with matrilin-1 (By similarity). Interacts with COMP. Component of a complex containing at least CRELD2, MANF, MATN3 and PDIA4 (By similarity).TISSUE SPECIFICITY Expressed only in cartilaginous tissues, such as vertebrae, ribs and shoulders.</bp:comment>
  </bp:ProteinReference>
